   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.5512_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>8 Southwell <abbr>Gns</abbr></addrLine>
                  <addrLine>S. W.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1874-12-07">7.12.74</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My dear Mr Hardy,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I only write two lines. 1st to congratulate you most sincerely on your marriage &amp;
               to wish you all happiness in that state. <unclear>Secondly</unclear> to say that I
               will write again soon about the novel. <!-- Need to reference which novel. FFMC? -->
               <del>May</del> I hope that we may arrange for May or June; but you shall hear
               soon.</p>

            <p> Meanwhile, if you are coming to town any day, I <choice><abbr>shd</abbr>
                  <expan>should</expan></choice> be much obliged if you would give me a call &amp;
               talk over the matter a little.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
               <signed>L. Stephen</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.5512_2.jpg"/>
            <!-- No text on this page other than H. number -->

         </div>
